User GuidePower on/off and select mode:Hold function button for a couple of seconds to turn the device on or off.There are four available modes:1: Basic mode2: Advanced mode3: Advanced mode- with pocket operator sync output enabled4: Advanced mode- with MIDI clock output enabledTo switch modes the device should be turned on and not playing.Hold function+play for a couple of seconds, 1-4 top leds will start to flash to indicate selected mode. Press +/- to select mode, or use the track buttons. Then press play to confirm.Basic mode functionality:Press play to pay/pause.Press +/- to control master volume.Use faders to set volume for individual stems.Use rocker to skip track forward and backward. Hold function and use rocket to fast forward or rewind playback.Funtion+Play will toggle slow playback.Track buttons will solo individual stems.Function+Track buttons will activate an audio effect on corresponding stem.Only gate effect is used in basic mode.Bluetooth:Hold both plus and minus buttons for a couple of seconds to scan for neaby Bluetooth speakers and headphones.Scanning is indicated on the side leds.Note: If the device is restarted, it might take up to 30s before bluetooth device reconnects.Advanced mode functionality:Click shortly on function button to enter track selection.The top leds will start pulsating. Then press a track button to select active track.Active track might also be selected by holding function and using volume bottons to select track. The currently seleted active track is indicated with solid light on top leds while the other tracks show VU meter instesity.Hold function+track to activate effects on active track.The effects are:1: Filter2: Chorus/Delay3: Distortion4: GateWhen holding a track button to activate effect, volume buttons select fx variation. Each effect has four variations.If Chorus/Delay is selected the first two variations are Chorus and the other two are Delay.Press and hold play button to activate loop.Loop mode is indicated on side leds.While holding play, use volume buttons to set loop divider and use rocker to move loop.Looping is disabled when play button is released (if not latched).Press play to abort loop mode latch.When not looping, use function+volume buttons to set loop divider.While using the rocker to reverse or fast forward playback, use volume buttons to select playback speed. When holding track or play or rocker, a short press on function will latch active functions (fx/loop/ffwd/rew).A short click on function when soloing one track will also remove latched fx on that track.Press play to unlatch loop.Use rocker to unlatch ffwd/rew.When paused, the side leds will indicate batter charge level.The device will automatically turn off after a couple of minutes if not playing.Connections:Connect headphones to audio jack. Built in speaker is muted.Speaker is also muted if a bluetooth receiver is connected.Connect USB type-C to charge the battery.Charging is indicated on side leds when device is turned off. There is no charging indication when charging is complete and the battery is full.Pocket operator syncSet the device in mode 3.Connect pocket operator to sync jack.Set the PO sync mode to SY2.MIDI clockSet the device in mode 4.Connect a MIDI clock receiver to 3.5mm midi jack.Or use a 3.5mm to DIN MIDI connector adapter.